      "writtenOn": "2018-07-11T00:19:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yes. This is exact for GL_EXT_texture_format_BGRA8888 extension. \n\nAnd actually,  GL_EXT_texture_format_BGRA8888  was supported by most gles driver. somebody\nsaid in 2014:  GL_EXT_texture_format_BGRA8888 extension supported by 98% of devices according to OpenGL ES Hardware Database\n\n\nBasically,  for GLES spec,  GL_RGBA + GL_BGRA is a bad combination and won\u0027t be acceptable by GLES driver.\n\nBut for desktop GL,  GL_BGRA + GL_BGRA is a bad combination and won\u0027t be acceptbale by OpenGL driver.\n\nSo the idea here is, since emulator is providing a GLES dispatcher, so it should accept \nGL_BGRA + GL_BGRA combination,  and then change internal format back to GL_RGBA for desktop gl backend.",
      "parentUuid": "260cc0d8_9cc4eac6",
